==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek ''meros'' "part" + ''onoma'' "name"

===Noun===
'''meronym'''
# A [[word]] that represents a [[part]] of a [[whole]].
#: ''Examples'':
#:: ''arm is a meronym of body''
#:: ''letter is a meronym of word''

